{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-post-template-js","path":"/posts/py-if-statements","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"id":"9823da8d-d198-5fb9-8cfd-2c634937e625","html":"<ul>\n<li><a href=\"#syntax\">Syntax</a></li>\n<li>\n<p><a href=\"#else-and-elif\">Else and Elif</a></p>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"#else\">Else</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#elif\">Elif</a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li><a href=\"#related\">Related</a></li>\n</ul>\n<p>An if statement in python uses the keyword if, then the block of code that the if statement runs is denoted by indentation. An if statement is useful when you want to redirect the flow of your program and act accordingly to user input.</p>\n<h2 id=\"syntax\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#syntax\" aria-label=\"syntax permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Syntax</h2>\n<p>Python if statements follow the syntax:</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"python\"><pre class=\"language-python\"><code class=\"language-python\"><span class=\"token keyword\">if</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>condition<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span>\n  <span class=\"token keyword\">print</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token string\">\"hello\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span>\n  var <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token number\">2</span>\n\n<span class=\"token keyword\">print</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token string\">\"Output this regardless if T or F\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span></code></pre></div>\n<ol>\n<li><code class=\"language-text\">if(condition)</code> - <code class=\"language-text\">condition</code> can be any boolean variable or logical condition</li>\n<li><code class=\"language-text\">print(&quot;hello&quot;)</code> and <code class=\"language-text\">var = 2</code> - These two lines are indented, which means this scope is what the if statement will run if the condition is true</li>\n<li><code class=\"language-text\">print(&quot;Output this regardless if T or F&quot;)</code> - This will be outputted regardless whether the condition is true or false</li>\n</ol>\n<h2 id=\"else-and-elif\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#else-and-elif\" aria-label=\"else and elif permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Else and Elif</h2>\n<h3 id=\"else\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#else\" aria-label=\"else permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Else</h3>\n<p>An else statement runs when the initial condition inside the <code class=\"language-text\">if</code> is false. For example:</p>\n<p>Example 1:</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"python\"><pre class=\"language-python\"><code class=\"language-python\">number <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token number\">2</span>\n\n<span class=\"token keyword\">if</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>number <span class=\"token operator\">+</span> <span class=\"token number\">3</span> <span class=\"token operator\">==</span> <span class=\"token number\">5</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span>\n  <span class=\"token keyword\">print</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token string\">\"The condition is true\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span>\n<span class=\"token keyword\">else</span>\n  <span class=\"token keyword\">print</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token string\">\"The condition is false\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span></code></pre></div>\n<p>Output 1:</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"text\"><pre class=\"language-text\"><code class=\"language-text\">The condition is true</code></pre></div>\n<p>The condition is true because 2 + 3 is equal to 5.</p>\n<p>Example 2:</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"python\"><pre class=\"language-python\"><code class=\"language-python\">number <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token number\">3</span>\n\n<span class=\"token keyword\">if</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>number <span class=\"token operator\">+</span> <span class=\"token number\">3</span> <span class=\"token operator\">==</span> <span class=\"token number\">5</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span>\n  <span class=\"token keyword\">print</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token string\">\"The condition is true\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span>\n<span class=\"token keyword\">else</span>\n  <span class=\"token keyword\">print</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token string\">\"The condition is false\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span></code></pre></div>\n<p>Output 2:</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"text\"><pre class=\"language-text\"><code class=\"language-text\">The condition is false</code></pre></div>\n<p>The condition is false because 3 + 3 is NOT equal to 5.</p>\n<h3 id=\"elif\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#elif\" aria-label=\"elif permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Elif</h3>\n<p>Elif is short for “else if”, think of it as like another else statement that runs when the if statement is false, but it also allows you to check for another condition.</p>\n<p>Example 3:</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"python\"><pre class=\"language-python\"><code class=\"language-python\">number <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token number\">7</span>\n\n<span class=\"token keyword\">if</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>number <span class=\"token operator\">+</span> <span class=\"token number\">2</span> <span class=\"token operator\">==</span> <span class=\"token number\">5</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span>\n  <span class=\"token keyword\">print</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token string\">\"The condition is true\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span>\n<span class=\"token keyword\">elif</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>number <span class=\"token operator\">==</span> <span class=\"token number\">5</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span>\n  <span class=\"token keyword\">print</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token string\">\"The number is 5\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span>\n<span class=\"token keyword\">elif</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>number <span class=\"token operator\">==</span> <span class=\"token number\">7</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span>\n  <span class=\"token keyword\">print</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token string\">\"The number is 7\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span>\n<span class=\"token keyword\">else</span>\n  <span class=\"token keyword\">print</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token string\">\"All of the conditions are false\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span></code></pre></div>\n<p>Output 3:</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"text\"><pre class=\"language-text\"><code class=\"language-text\">The number is 7</code></pre></div>\n<h2 id=\"related\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#related\" aria-label=\"related permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Related:</h2>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"/posts/py-hello-world\">Python - Installation Hello World</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/posts/cpp-hello-world\">C++ - Hello World</a></li>\n</ul>","fields":{"slug":"/posts/py-if-statements","tagSlugs":["/tag/python/","/tag/tutorial/","/tag/if/","/tag/flow-control/"]},"frontmatter":{"date":"2020-10-12T16:25:03+08:00","description":"An if statement in python uses the keyword if, then the block of code that the if statement runs is denoted by indentation. An if statement is useful when you want to redirect the flow of your program and act accordingly to user input","tags":["Python","Tutorial","If","Flow Control"],"title":"Python If Statements","socialImage":null}}},"pageContext":{"slug":"/posts/py-if-statements"}},"staticQueryHashes":["251939775","3942705351","401334301"]}